    "department": "Engineering",
    "description": "COPERNIQ https://www.coperniq.io\n\nAbout Us: Coperniq is on a mission to revolutionize the renewable energy industry with cutting-edge software solutions. As a Y Combinator-backed startup, funded by Initialized Capital, we’re building the infrastructure for clean energy contractors to succeed.\n\nRole Overview: We’re looking for a Senior Mobile Engineer to lead the development of our mobile platform. As the only engineer on a small team that includes a QA Architect and a Senior Designer, you’ll play a pivotal role in shaping our mobile experience. This is a unique opportunity to build from the ground up while collaborating closely with design and QA to deliver a world-class product. If you have experience shipping robust mobile applications and thrive in a dynamic, high-impact environment, we’d love to meet you.\n\nWhat You’ll Do:\n\n - Architect, develop, and maintain our mobile applications for iOS and Android.\n\n - Collaborate with design and QA to deliver seamless and polished user experiences.\n\n - Define and implement best practices for mobile development, testing, and deployment.\n\n - Own technical decisions and ensure the scalability of our mobile platform.\n\n - Act as the main point of technical expertise for all things mobile.\n\nWhat We’re Looking For:\n\n - 5+ years of professional experience in mobile app development.\n\n - Expertise in React Native or native development for iOS/Android.\n\n - Proven track record of shipping high-quality mobile apps to production.\n\n - Strong understanding of mobile performance optimization and debugging.\n\n - Ability to thrive as the sole engineer in a collaborative, small-team environment.\n\n - Excellent English skills and a proactive approach to problem-solving.\n\nNice to Have:\n\n - Experience in the renewable energy or SaaS industry.\n\n - Knowledge of geolocation technologies and real-time data integration.\n\n - Familiarity with SOC II compliance and secure app development practices.\n\nWhat We Offer:\n\n - Competitive salary and equity.\n\n - Flexible work environment with opportunities for remote work.\n\n - The chance to shape the future of clean energy.\n\n - A collaborative, high-performance team culture\n\nProcess:\n\n - Silver Recruiter Screen\n\n - Live Coding Interview\n\n - Technical Interview with client\n\n - CTO Interview\n\n - CEO Interview (Final round)",
